<ol><li>Liquid molecules <b>slow down</b> as the liquid cools.</li><li>At the melting point, the molecules move slowly enough for the force bonds to&nbsp;<b>lock the molecules together</b>.</li><li><b>Latent heat is released </b>when a liquid solidifes, and&nbsp;<b>keeps the temperature at the melting point</b>&nbsp;until all the liquid has solidified.</li></ol>